    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Inventing a 3% discrepancy is a bit of a red flag, rather like a small, insidious goblin lurking in the shadows, waiting to pounce. You'll want to investigate further to determine the source of the discrepancy. Standard auditing methods to identify the loss include conducting a physical inventory count, reviewing security footage, analyzing sales data, and interviewing employees to identify potential discrepancies in their records. It's also essential to consider the possibility of internal theft, a sneaky goblin that can be particularly hard to detect.",
